    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="R000004" softwareId="23018249" softwareVersionNum="v1.00">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990-EZ, Part I, Line 10</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Received donations of unused computer equipment. As the company was intending to dissolve, the donations were transferred to various GoodWill Stores. The stores provided "cages" for the equipment to be stored in, and the equipment was loaded into the cages and GoodWill picked up the cages.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990-EZ, Part V, Line 33</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The donation of equipment wasn't a normal function of the ministry, but the ministry was in the process of terminating operations, so the equipment was nonetheless donated to GoodWill for their programs to ensure a proper public benefit from the donated equipment.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990-EZ, Part V, Line 34</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The ministry merged from an Idaho Corporation to an Iowa corporation. The IRS wouldn't allow a new EIN to be issued to the Ministry after it completed the merger, so for purposes of this filing, the merger is treated as a redomiciliation.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleO>
